  "response_text": "# Healthy Eating Plan for Busy Single Parents\n\n## Weekly Strategy\n\n**Prep once, eat multiple times**\n- Sunday: 2-3 hours of cooking\n- Freeze portions in individual containers\n- Aim for 3-4 base recipes per week\n\n## Easy Meal Framework\n\n### Breakfasts (minimal prep)\n- Overnight oats (make 5 jars Sunday)\n- Scrambled eggs + fruit\n- Whole grain toast + nut butter\n- Yogurt parfaits\n\n### Lunches (batch-friendly)\n- Sheet pan chicken with roasted vegetables\n- Slow cooker chili or soup\n- Grain bowls (rice + protein + veggies)\n- Pasta with hidden veggie sauce\n\n### Dinners (30 min or less)\n- One-pot meals (stir-fries, curries)\n- Slow cooker dishes (set before work)\n- Rotisserie chicken + simple sides\n- Tacos or sheet pan meals\n\n### Snacks\n- Hard-boiled eggs\n- Fruit + cheese\n- Hummus + veggies\n- Nuts, popcorn\n\n## Shopping Shortcuts\n\n**Buy pre-prepped:**\n- Pre-cut vegetables\n- Rotisserie chicken\n- Canned beans\n- Frozen vegetables (just as nutritious)\n\n**Pantry staples:**\n- Canned tomatoes, beans, broth\n- Pasta, rice, oats\n- Spices and sauces\n\n## Time-Saving Tips\n\n- Use a slow cooker (meals ready when you arrive home)\n- Double recipes for leftovers\n- Involve kids in simple tasks (builds skills + buys time)\n- Keep it simple—5 ingredients is enough\n- Accept \"good enough\" over perfect\n\nWould you like specific recipes or help adapting this to dietary preferences?",
